# "When a new trigger arrives while the current burst is still ongoing, it will
# not be finished but restarted from the beginning immediately."
# Same params as basic-burst (tickrate 8, hz 1, count 3). Trigger at t1 begins
# pulse 1 (t1..t4 high). A second trigger at t5 restarts the burst from phase 0,
# so t5..t8 is a NEW pulse 1 -- WITHOUT the restart t5..t8 would be low (the
# original burst's low half). The tell is 5 consecutive highs t4..t8: the
# original burst alone only ever produces 4-tick-wide pulses.
tickrate 8
patch <<<
[burst]
    trigger = I1
    hz      = 1
    count   = 3
    output  = O1
>>>
@0 expect O1 0
@1 set I1 1
@1 expect O1 1
@2 set I1 0
@2 expect O1 1
@3 expect O1 1
@4 expect O1 1
@5 set I1 1
@5 expect O1 1
@6 set I1 0
@6 expect O1 1
@7 expect O1 1
@8 expect O1 1
@9 expect O1 0
@10 expect O1 0
@11 expect O1 0
@12 expect O1 0
@13 expect O1 1
@14 expect O1 1
@15 expect O1 1
@16 expect O1 1
@17 expect O1 0
